2 unit Scallions
1 unit Mini Cucumber
8 ounce Pulled Pork
4 tablespoon Hoisin Sauce
1 teaspoon Sriracha
1 tablespoon Sesame Seeds
1 unit Baby Lettuce
1 unit Lime
¼ ounce Cilantro
1 unit Crispy Fried Onions
½ teaspoon Sugar
Salt

• Wash and dry produce.

• Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens. Trim and slice
cucumber lengthwise into ¼-inch-thick planks, then cut crosswise into
¼-inch-thick matchsticks.

• Place pulled pork* in a medium microwave-safe bowl. Using two forks, break
up pork into smaller pieces; stir in scallion whites, hoisin, Sriracha, and half the
sesame seeds. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave until warmed through,
2-3 minutes.

• Meanwhile, trim and discard root end from lettuce; separate leaves. Reserve
six whole leaves for serving (twelve whole leaves for 4 servings); thinly slice
remaining leaves. Halve lime.

• In a second medium bowl, combine cucumber, scallion greens, remaining
sesame seeds, ½ tsp sugar (1 tsp for 4 servings), juice from the lime, and a
pinch of salt.

• Pick cilantro leaves from stems; tear leaves into pieces. Divide whole lettuce
leaves between plates and fill with shredded lettuce, pork filling, and as
much marinated cucumber as you like (draining first). Sprinkle with cilantro
and crispy fried onions. Serve any remaining marinated cucumber on the side.

***Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.***